Statoil’s Lund ‘Optimistic’ on Brazil, Dagens Naeringsliv Says

-- B y   J o s i a n e   K r e m e r
-- 
2011-05-28T13:20:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/statoil-s-lund-optimistic-on-brazil-dagens-naeringsliv-says.html
Statoil ASA (STL)  is “optimistic” the  oil
company  can enter the second development phase of the Brazilian
Peregrino field soon,  Dagens Naeringsliv reported , citing Chief
Executive Helge Lund.  The company will need six to 12 months to “get clarity”
on the project, the Oslo-based newspaper cited Lund as saying.  Kjetil Hove, Statoil’s head of operations for Brazil, said
on May 25 that the Stavanger, Norway-based company plans to
drill eight exploration wells in the South American nation
within 18 months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Josiane Kremer in Oslo at 
 jkremer4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
